-- Santander Brasil beats second-quarter profit estimates 
-- 
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 06:38AM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, July 31 (Reuters) - Banco Santander Brasil SA <SANB11.SA> posted on Wednesday second-quarter profit that beat analysts' estimates.

Recurring net income, or profit after one-time items, reached 1.437 billion reais ($641 million) in the quarter, well above the average estimate of 1.280 billion reais in a Reuters poll of four analysts. Recurring return on equity, a gauge of profitability, was 11.6 percent in the second quarter, compared with 9.7 percent in the poll.